# Documentation Requirements

## On Every Change

After modifying code, update the relevant documentation:

1. **New feature or behavior** → Update `docs/features.md` (relevant section)
2. **Bug fix** → Add entry to `docs/errors.md` with cause, fix, prevention
3. **Architecture change** → Update `docs/architecture.md` with decision record
4. **New CLI command or option** → Update README.md CLI Reference table
5. **New API endpoint** → Update `docs/features.md` Admin API section
6. **New UI page or component** → Update `docs/features.md` Admin UI section
7. **Infrastructure change** → Update `docs/features.md` Infrastructure section

## On Every Error Resolution

Always add to `docs/errors.md`:

```markdown
### [Descriptive Title]
**Category**: Build | Deploy | CI | Runtime | Auth | Infra
**Symptom**: What happens
**Cause**: Why it happens
**Fix**: How to fix it
**Prevention**: How to prevent it
```

## Commit Message Convention

```
feat: add new feature
fix: resolve bug
docs: update documentation
chore: maintenance task
refactor: code restructuring
```

## Self-Improvement Loop

1. Error occurs → fix it → document in `docs/errors.md`
2. Pattern emerges → add rule to `.cursor/rules/`
3. Workflow changes → update relevant skill in `.cursor/skills/`
4. Feature added → update `docs/features.md` + README.md
5. AWS/credential issue → update deploy skill + README credential section
6. **Never make the same mistake twice** — always check `docs/errors.md` before debugging

## Agent Pre-checks (ALWAYS do before acting)

1. **AWS commands** → `lyx aws status` — if expired, run `lyx aws login`
2. **CLI commands** → `which lyx` — if not found, rebuild and link
3. **Directory renames** → `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile` + commit lockfile
4. **After fixing anything** → update `docs/errors.md` with the resolution
5. **Before committing** → Run `pnpm test` (unit) + `pnpm test:e2e` (E2E) — ALL MUST PASS
6. **New feature** → Add Playwright E2E tests in `tests/e2e/admin/` or `tests/e2e/shell/`
7. **Performance-sensitive change** → Run `pnpm test:k6:all` before deploying
